 can be simplified to
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
0=v\left(m_{H}^{2}-\frac{\lambda}{3}v^{2}\right)+\mathcal{O}\left(\lambda^{2}\right).
\end{equation}

\end_inset

In the symmetric regime 
\begin_inset Formula $v=0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{H}^{2}-m_{G}^{2}=\frac{\hbar\lambda}{3}\left(\mathcal{T}_{H}^{\mathrm{fin}}-\mathcal{T}_{G}^{\mathrm{fin}}\right)$
\end_inset

 which has the solution 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{H}^{2}=m_{G}^{2}=m^{2}+\frac{\hbar\lambda}{6}\left(N+2\right)\mathcal{T}_{G}^{\mathrm{fin}}+\mathcal{O}\left(\lambda^{2}\right)$
\end_inset

.
 The critical temperature 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{\star}$
\end_inset

 occurs when 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{H}^{2}=m_{G}^{2}=0$
\end_inset

, for which 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{T}_{G}^{\mathrm{fin}}=T_{\star}^{2}/12$
\end_inset

, giving
\end_layout

